Class Header

java.lang.Object
  inedi.Header

public class Header
extends java.lang.Object

An HTTP header as it is received from the server.

When a header is received through a Header event, it is parsed into a header type. This type contains a Field , and its corresponding Value .

Field: This field contains the name of the HTTP header (same case as it is delivered).

Value: This field contains the header contents.

See Also:
As1receiver, As1receiver.Header
